name: Blue Bloods
summary: The finale of the long-running police drama "Blue Bloods" has sparked much discussion. Donnie Wahlberg, who plays Detective Danny Reagan, fought for a certain outcome for his character and Detective Maria Baez. There is speculation about when the series will officially end, with some sources suggesting a final episode in the near future. Tom Selleck, who plays Police Commissioner Frank Reagan, delivered poignant final words in the family dinner scene that concluded the episode. Showrunner Kevin Wade has spoken about the significance of this last meal, the Reagans' future, and the possibility of spin-offs. The episode included a wedding, a pregnancy announcement, and a death, leaving fans with mixed emotions. The series finale has garnered a range of reactions, with some viewers expressing their satisfaction and others sharing their disappointment. Donnie Wahlberg has penned a tribute to the cast and crew, expressing his gratitude for their time together.
